<img src="../images/rexona.jpg" alt="Rexona Project">

<h2>Description</h2>

<p>
Led the complete transformation of the Rexona soap packing cascade through a phased automation strategy to improve productivity, quality and labour efficiency.
</p>

<h2>Key Actions</h2>

<ul>
<li>Commissioned refurbished cartoning machine.</li>
<li>Automated tablet feeding using pick-and-place technology.</li>
<li>Implemented end-of-line automation.</li>
<li>Modified idle equipment for reuse.</li>
<li>Eliminated quality defects through process redesign.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Key Results</h2>

<ul>
<li>Capacity increased to 90 units per minute.</li>
<li>Reduced manpower from 14 to 4 operators.</li>
<li>Achieved 71% labour reduction.</li>
<li>Improved productivity and OEE.</li>
<li>Reduced quality defects.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Skills Gained</h2>

<p>
Automation • Mechanical Design • Equipment Commissioning • Lean Manufacturing • Project Engineering
